{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1142,"text":"I once said,"},{"time":2849,"text":"\"If you want to liberate a society,"},{"time":5507,"text":"all you need is the Internet.\""},{"time":8261,"text":"I was wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10121,"text":"I said those words back in 2011,"},{"time":12725,"text":"when a Facebook page I anonymously created"},{"time":15671,"text":"helped spark the Egyptian revolution."},{"time":18724,"text":"The Arab Spring revealed\nsocial media's greatest potential,"},{"time":23328,"text":"but it also exposed\nits greatest shortcomings."},{"time":28003,"text":"The same tool that united us\nto topple dictators"},{"time":33055,"text":"eventually tore us apart."},{"time":36229,"text":"I would like to share my own experience\nin using social media for activism,"},{"time":41148,"text":"and talk about some of the challenges\nI have personally faced"},{"time":44703,"text":"and what we could do about them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47818,"text":"In the early 2000s,"},{"time":50334,"text":"Arabs were flooding the web."},{"time":53619,"text":"Thirsty for knowledge, for opportunities,"},{"time":56604,"text":"for connecting with the rest\nof the people around the globe,"},{"time":60340,"text":"we escaped our frustrating\npolitical realities"},{"time":64735,"text":"and lived a virtual, alternative life."},{"time":69684,"text":"Just like many of them,\nI was completely apolitical until 2009."},{"time":74835,"text":"At the time, when I logged\ninto social media,"},{"time":78368,"text":"I started seeing more and more Egyptians"},{"time":80912,"text":"aspiring for political change\nin the country."},{"time":84244,"text":"It felt like I was not alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88577,"text":"In June 2010,"},{"time":90308,"text":"Internet changed my life forever."},{"time":95055,"text":"While browsing Facebook,"},{"time":98263,"text":"I saw a photo, a terrifying photo,\nof a tortured, dead body"},{"time":103493,"text":"of a young Egyptian guy."},{"time":105891,"text":"His name was Khaled Said."},{"time":109080,"text":"Khaled was a 29-year-old Alexandrian\nwho was killed by police."},{"time":115099,"text":"I saw myself in his picture."},{"time":117924,"text":"I thought, \"I could be Khaled.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":120853,"text":"I could not sleep that night,\nand I decided to do something."},{"time":125542,"text":"I anonymously created a Facebook page"},{"time":128067,"text":"and called it \"We are all Khaled Said.\""},{"time":132645,"text":"In just three days, the page\nhad over 100,000 people,"},{"time":137294,"text":"fellow Egyptians who shared\nthe same concern."},{"time":141390,"text":"Whatever was happening had to stop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144631,"text":"I recruited my co-admin,\nAbdelRahman Mansour."},{"time":148059,"text":"We worked together for hours and hours."},{"time":150956,"text":"We were crowdsourcing\nideas from the people."},{"time":153908,"text":"We were engaging them."},{"time":155376,"text":"We were calling collectively for actions,"},{"time":157964,"text":"and sharing news that the regime\ndid not want Egyptians to know."},{"time":162733,"text":"The page became the most followed page"},{"time":165721,"text":"in the Arab world."},{"time":167148,"text":"It had more fans than established\nmedia organizations"},{"time":171526,"text":"and even top celebrities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174468,"text":"On January 14, 2011,"},{"time":177555,"text":"Ben Ali fled out of Tunisia"},{"time":180112,"text":"after mounting protests\nagainst his regime."},{"time":183589,"text":"I saw a spark of hope."},{"time":186144,"text":"Egyptians on social media were wondering,"},{"time":189350,"text":"\"If Tunisia did it, why can't we?\""},{"time":192715,"text":"I posted an event\non Facebook and called it"},{"time":194931,"text":"\"A Revolution against Corruption,\nInjustice and Dictatorship.\""},{"time":200635,"text":"I posed a question to the 300,000 users\nof the page at the time:"},{"time":205685,"text":"\"Today is the 14th of January."},{"time":208969,"text":"The 25th of January is Police Day."},{"time":212580,"text":"It's a national holiday."},{"time":214283,"text":"If 100,000 of us take\nto the streets of Cairo,"},{"time":218251,"text":"no one is going to stop us."},{"time":220030,"text":"I wonder if we could do it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":222797,"text":"In just a few days, the invitation\nreached over a million people,"},{"time":227303,"text":"and over 100,000 people\nconfirmed attendance."},{"time":231562,"text":"Social media was crucial\nfor this campaign."},{"time":234329,"text":"It helped a decentralized movement arise."},{"time":237999,"text":"It made people realize\nthat they were not alone."},{"time":240927,"text":"And it made it impossible\nfor the regime to stop it."},{"time":244259,"text":"At the time, they didn't\neven understand it."},{"time":247656,"text":"And on January 25th, Egyptians flooded\nthe streets of Cairo and other cities,"},{"time":253913,"text":"calling for change,"},{"time":255911,"text":"breaking the barrier of fear"},{"time":258230,"text":"and announcing a new era."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261947,"text":"Then came the consequences."},{"time":264592,"text":"A few hours before the regime cut off\nthe Internet and telecommunications,"},{"time":269395,"text":"I was walking in a dark street\nin Cairo, around midnight."},{"time":274075,"text":"I had just tweeted, \"Pray for Egypt."},{"time":277423,"text":"The government must be planning\na massacre tomorrow.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":281587,"text":"I was hit hard on my head."},{"time":284589,"text":"I lost my balance and fell down,"},{"time":286723,"text":"to find four armed men surrounding me."},{"time":290698,"text":"One covered my mouth\nand the others paralyzed me."},{"time":294711,"text":"I knew I was being kidnapped\nby state security."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298701,"text":"I found myself in a cell,"},{"time":302259,"text":"handcuffed, blindfolded."},{"time":305027,"text":"I was terrified."},{"time":306615,"text":"So was my family,"},{"time":308956,"text":"who started looking for me"},{"time":310605,"text":"in hospitals, police stations\nand even morgues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314569,"text":"After my disappearance,"},{"time":315864,"text":"a few of my fellow colleagues who knew\nI was the admin of the page"},{"time":319277,"text":"told the media about\nmy connection with that page,"},{"time":323500,"text":"and that I was likely arrested\nby state security."},{"time":327189,"text":"My colleagues at Google started\na search campaign trying to find me,"},{"time":331596,"text":"and the fellow protesters in the square\ndemanded my release."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336088,"text":"After 11 days of complete darkness,"},{"time":338564,"text":"I was set free."},{"time":340516,"text":"And three days later,"},{"time":342152,"text":"Mubarak was forced to step down."},{"time":345505,"text":"It was the most inspiring\nand empowering moment of my life."},{"time":350633,"text":"It was a time of great hope."},{"time":353265,"text":"Egyptians lived a utopia for 18 days\nduring the revolution."},{"time":357685,"text":"They all shared the belief"},{"time":359581,"text":"that we could actually live together\ndespite our differences,"},{"time":363897,"text":"that Egypt after Mubarak would be for all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367267,"text":"But unfortunately,"},{"time":368538,"text":"the post-revolution events\nwere like a punch in the gut."},{"time":374609,"text":"The euphoria faded,"},{"time":376775,"text":"we failed to build consensus,"},{"time":379840,"text":"and the political struggle\nled to intense polarization."},{"time":383813,"text":"Social media only amplified that state,"},{"time":386626,"text":"by facilitating the spread\nof misinformation, rumors,"},{"time":390803,"text":"echo chambers and hate speech."},{"time":393189,"text":"The environment was purely toxic."},{"time":396265,"text":"My online world became a battleground\nfilled with trolls, lies, hate speech."},{"time":403660,"text":"I started to worry\nabout the safety of my family."},{"time":407655,"text":"But of course, this wasn't just about me."},{"time":411145,"text":"The polarization reached its peak\nbetween the two main powers --"},{"time":416093,"text":"the army supporters and the Islamists."},{"time":418986,"text":"People in the center, like me,"},{"time":421418,"text":"started feeling helpless."},{"time":424587,"text":"Both groups wanted you to side with them;"},{"time":427111,"text":"you were either with them or against them."},{"time":430737,"text":"And on the 3rd of July 2013,"},{"time":432663,"text":"the army ousted Egypt's first\ndemocratically elected president,"},{"time":437194,"text":"after three days of popular protest\nthat demanded his resignation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442519,"text":"That day I made a very hard decision."},{"time":445688,"text":"I decided to go silent, completely silent."},{"time":450106,"text":"It was a moment of defeat."},{"time":453101,"text":"I stayed silent for more than two years,"},{"time":455929,"text":"and I used the time to reflect\non everything that happened,"},{"time":459394,"text":"trying to understand why did it happen."},{"time":462773,"text":"It became clear to me"},{"time":464242,"text":"that while it's true that polarization\nis primarily driven"},{"time":469187,"text":"by our human behavior,"},{"time":471046,"text":"social media shapes this behavior\nand magnifies its impact."},{"time":476315,"text":"Say you want to say something\nthat is not based on a fact,"},{"time":479430,"text":"pick a fight or ignore\nsomeone that you don't like."},{"time":482914,"text":"These are all natural human impulses,"},{"time":485645,"text":"but because of technology,"},{"time":487824,"text":"acting on these impulses\nis only one click away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492562,"text":"In my view, there are five\ncritical challenges"},{"time":495529,"text":"facing today's social media."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498794,"text":"First, we don't know\nhow to deal with rumors."},{"time":502493,"text":"Rumors that confirm people's biases"},{"time":505243,"text":"are now believed and spread\namong millions of people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510590,"text":"Second, we create our own echo chambers."},{"time":514595,"text":"We tend to only communicate\nwith people that we agree with,"},{"time":517936,"text":"and thanks to social media,"},{"time":520124,"text":"we can mute, un-follow\nand block everybody else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526247,"text":"Third, online discussions\nquickly descend into angry mobs."},{"time":531571,"text":"All of us probably know that."},{"time":533833,"text":"It's as if we forget"},{"time":535651,"text":"that the people behind screens\nare actually real people"},{"time":538935,"text":"and not just avatars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541254,"text":"And fourth, it became really hard\nto change our opinions."},{"time":546309,"text":"Because of the speed\nand brevity of social media,"},{"time":549617,"text":"we are forced to jump to conclusions"},{"time":552575,"text":"and write sharp opinions in 140 characters"},{"time":555663,"text":"about complex world affairs."},{"time":558402,"text":"And once we do that,\nit lives forever on the Internet,"},{"time":562276,"text":"and we are less motivated\nto change these views,"},{"time":565403,"text":"even when new evidence arises."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568033,"text":"Fifth -- and in my point of view,\nthis is the most critical --"},{"time":572246,"text":"today, our social media experiences\nare designed in a way"},{"time":576574,"text":"that favors broadcasting over engagements,"},{"time":579535,"text":"posts over discussions,"},{"time":582586,"text":"shallow comments over deep conversations."},{"time":585764,"text":"It's as if we agreed that\nwe are here to talk at each other"},{"time":589838,"text":"instead of talking with each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593244,"text":"I witnessed how these\ncritical challenges contributed"},{"time":595704,"text":"to an already polarized\nEgyptian society,"},{"time":599041,"text":"but this is not just about Egypt."},{"time":601601,"text":"Polarization is on the rise\nin the whole world."},{"time":605325,"text":"We need to work hard on figuring out"},{"time":607923,"text":"how technology could be\npart of the solution,"},{"time":611268,"text":"rather than part of the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615072,"text":"There's a lot of debate today\non how to combat online harassment"},{"time":618436,"text":"and fight trolls."},{"time":619992,"text":"This is so important."},{"time":621818,"text":"No one could argue against that."},{"time":624251,"text":"But we need to also think about how\nto design social media experiences"},{"time":629492,"text":"that promote civility\nand reward thoughtfulness."},{"time":633512,"text":"I know for a fact"},{"time":634906,"text":"if I write a post\nthat is more sensational,"},{"time":638146,"text":"more one-sided, sometimes\nangry and aggressive,"},{"time":641681,"text":"I get to have more people see that post."},{"time":644791,"text":"I will get more attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647726,"text":"But what if we put more focus on quality?"},{"time":651149,"text":"What is more important:"},{"time":652398,"text":"the total number of readers\nof a post you write,"},{"time":655075,"text":"or who are the people who have impact\nthat read what you write?"},{"time":660846,"text":"Couldn't we just give people more\nincentives to engage in conversations,"},{"time":665236,"text":"rather than just broadcasting\nopinions all the time?"},{"time":668788,"text":"Or reward people for reading"},{"time":670210,"text":"and responding to views\nthat they disagree with?"},{"time":674082,"text":"And also, make it socially acceptable\nthat we change our minds,"},{"time":678819,"text":"or probably even reward that?"},{"time":681343,"text":"What if we have a matrix that says\nhow many people changed their minds,"},{"time":685516,"text":"and that becomes part\nof our social media experience?"},{"time":689206,"text":"If I could track how many people\nare changing their minds,"},{"time":692307,"text":"I'd probably write more\nthoughtfully, trying to do that,"},{"time":696032,"text":"rather than appealing to the people\nwho already agree with me"},{"time":699761,"text":"and \"liking\" because I just\nconfirmed their biases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703512,"text":"We also need to think about effective\ncrowdsourcing mechanisms,"},{"time":707192,"text":"to fact-check widely spread\nonline information,"},{"time":710941,"text":"and reward people who take part in that."},{"time":713924,"text":"In essence, we need to rethink\ntoday's social media ecosystem"},{"time":718885,"text":"and redesign its experiences"},{"time":721164,"text":"to reward thoughtfulness, civility\nand mutual understanding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725585,"text":"As a believer in the Internet,\nI teamed up with a few friends,"},{"time":728867,"text":"started a new project,"},{"time":730374,"text":"trying to find answers\nand explore possibilities."},{"time":734630,"text":"Our first product is a new\nmedia platform for conversations."},{"time":738977,"text":"We're hosting conversations\nthat promote mutual understanding"},{"time":742263,"text":"and hopefully change minds."},{"time":744348,"text":"We don't claim to have the answers,"},{"time":746779,"text":"but we started experimenting\nwith different discussions"},{"time":750168,"text":"about very divisive issues,"},{"time":752255,"text":"such as race, gun control,\nthe refugee debate,"},{"time":756426,"text":"relationship between Islam and terrorism."},{"time":759217,"text":"These are conversations that matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762779,"text":"Today, at least one out of three\npeople on the planet"},{"time":767810,"text":"have access to the Internet."},{"time":770226,"text":"But part of this Internet\nis being held captive"},{"time":774050,"text":"by the less noble aspects\nof our human behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778774,"text":"Five years ago, I said,"},{"time":781148,"text":"\"If you want to liberate society,"},{"time":784943,"text":"all you need is the Internet.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":787207,"text":"Today, I believe if we want\nto liberate society,"},{"time":792266,"text":"we first need to liberate the Internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795193,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796385,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}